Ask the user for a number. Depending on whether the number is even or odd, print out an appropriate message to the user.

a) If the number is a multiple of 4, print out a different message.


num = int(input('Enter a number. '))
if num % 4 == 0:
    print('multiple of 4')
elif num % 2 == 0:   
    print('even')
else: 
    print('odd')
    
--------------------------------------------------------------
b) Ask the user for two numbers: one number to check (call it num) and one number to divide by (check). 
   If check divides evenly into num, tell that to the user. If not, print a different appropriate message.


num, check = input('Enter 2 numbers ').split()
if int(num) % int(check) == 0:
    print('evenly divided')
else:
    print('not evenly divided')
